<odoo>
  <record id="donations" model="ir.ui.view">
    <field name="name">Donations</field>
    <field name="key">museum.donations</field>
    <field name="type">qweb</field>
    <field name="website_id" ref="website.default_website"/>
    <field name="arch" type="xml">
      <t t-name="website.donations">
        <t t-call="website.layout">
          <div id="wrap" class="oe_structure oe_empty">
            <section class="s_parallax bg-black-50 o_colored_level s_parallax_no_overflow_hidden o_half_screen_height oe_img_bg o_bg_img_center o_bg_img_origin_border_box" data-scroll-background-ratio="0" data-snippet="s_parallax" data-name="Parallax" style="background-image: url('/web/image/museum.ir_attachment_1605') !important;">
              <div class="oe_structure oe_empty" data-editor-message-default="true" data-editor-message="DRAG BUILDING BLOCKS HERE"/>
            </section>
            <section class="s_text_block pt40 pb0 o_colored_level" data-snippet="s_text_block" data-name="Text">
              <div class="container s_allow_columns">
                <h1 style="text-align: center;">Support Us</h1>
              </div>
            </section>
            <section class="s_text_block pt40 pb40 o_colored_level" data-snippet="s_text_block" data-name="Text">
              <div class="container s_allow_columns">
                <h4>Preserve. Share. Inspire.</h4>
                <p>When you donate to the museum, you’re helping more than just a building or a collection. You’re supporting the care of fragile works, the digitization of rarely seen pieces, and the creation of exhibitions that ask timely questions. You’re making space for artists—past and present—whose work might otherwise go unheard.</p>
                <p>Your contribution helps us keep the museum open and accessible to everyone: students, families, researchers, and curious visitors of all ages. Whether it’s a one-time gift or ongoing support, your donation becomes part of the museum’s story—and part of what we pass on to future generations.</p>
              </div>
            </section>
            <section class="pt32 pb32 o_cc o_cc1 o_colored_level" data-snippet="s_donation" data-name="Donation">
              <div class="container">
                <div class="row align-items-center">
                  <div class="col-lg-7 pt16 pb16 o_colored_level">
                    <h2>Make a Donation</h2>
                    <p>Small or large, your contribution is essential.</p>
                    <p/>
                    <p><strong>Support a Cause</strong> — Donate to fund cause-related exhibitions.</p>
                    <p>
</p>
                    <p><strong>Adopt an Artwork</strong> — Fund conservation for specific engaged art pieces.</p>
                    <p>
</p>
                    <p><strong>Fund Free Access</strong> — Help us keep entry free for underprivileged groups.</p>
                    <p>
</p>
                    <p><strong>Monthly Ally</strong> — Join our core donors who fund art for awareness, monthly.</p>
                    <p>
                      <br/>
                    </p>
                    <div class="s_donation" data-name="Donation Button" data-donation-email="info@yourcompany.example.com" data-custom-amount="slider" data-descriptions="true" data-minimum-amount="5" data-maximum-amount="300" data-slider-step="1" data-default-amount="25" data-snippet="s_donation_button" data-display-options="true" data-prefilled-options="" data-donation-amounts="[&quot;100&quot;,&quot;50&quot;]">
                      <form class="s_donation_form" action="/donation/pay" method="post" enctype="multipart/form-data">
                        <span id="s_donation_description_inputs">
                          <input type="hidden" class="o_translatable_input_hidden d-block mb-1 w-100" name="donation_descriptions" value="Support a Cause: Donate to fund cause-related exhibitions."/>
                          <input type="hidden" class="o_translatable_input_hidden d-block mb-1 w-100" name="donation_descriptions" value="Add a description here"/>
                        </span>
                        <div class="s_donation_prefilled_buttons mb-2"/>
                        <div class="s_donation_range_slider_wrap mb-2 position-relative">
                          <label for="s_donation_range_slider">Choose Your Amount</label>
                          <input type="range" class="form-range" id="s_donation_range_slider" min="5" max="300" step="1"/>
                          <output class="s_range_bubble" style="inset-inline-start: calc(6.77966% + 6.91525px);">25</output>
                        </div>
                        <a href="#" type="button" class="s_donation_donate_btn btn btn-secondary btn-lg mb-2">Donate now</a>
                      </form>
                    </div>
                  </div>
                  <div class="col-lg-5 pt16 pb16 d-none d-md-block o_colored_level">
                    <img src="/web/image/museum.ir_attachment_1607" alt="woman in black shirt sitting on chair" class="img img-fluid mx-auto o_we_custom_image" style="width: 75%;" data-resize-width="undefined" loading="lazy"/>
                  </div>
                </div>
              </div>
            </section>
          </div>
        </t>
      </t>
    </field>
  </record>
  <record id="exhibitions" model="ir.ui.view">
    <field name="name">EXHIBITIONS</field>
    <field name="key">museum.exhibitions</field>
    <field name="type">qweb</field>
    <field name="website_id" ref="website.default_website"/>
    <field name="arch" type="xml">
      <t t-name="website.exhibitions">
        <t t-call="website.layout">
          <div id="wrap" class="oe_structure oe_empty">
            <section class="s_sidegrid pt56 pb56 o_colored_level" data-snippet="s_sidegrid" data-name="Side grid">
              <div class="container">
                <div class="row o_grid_mode" data-row-count="13">
                  <div class="o_grid_item o_grid_item_image g-height-4 g-col-lg-4 col-lg-4 o_colored_level" style="z-index: 2; grid-area: 1 / 1 / 5 / 5;">
                    <img src="/web/image/museum.ir_attachment_1595" alt="a building with multiple windows and a yellow door" class="img img-fluid o_we_custom_image" data-resize-width="undefined" loading="lazy"/>
                  </div>
                  <div class="o_grid_item o_grid_item_image o_snippet_mobile_invisible g-height-9 g-col-lg-3 col-lg-3 d-lg-block d-none o_colored_level" style="z-index: 3; grid-area: 1 / 5 / 10 / 8;">
                    <img src="/web/image/museum.ir_attachment_1584" alt="a building that has a very unusual design on it" class="img img-fluid o_we_custom_image" data-mimetype="image/webp" data-original-id="1145" data-original-src="/unsplash/ak99G4o0_0w/guggenheim.jpg?unique=c2fac036" data-mimetype-before-conversion="image/jpeg" data-resize-width="NaN" loading="lazy"/>
                  </div>
                  <div class="o_grid_item o_grid_item_image o_snippet_mobile_invisible g-height-9 g-col-lg-4 col-lg-4 d-lg-block d-none o_colored_level" style="z-index: 4; grid-area: 5 / 1 / 14 / 5;">
                    <img src="/web/image/museum.ir_attachment_1581" alt="person foot under painting" class="img img-fluid o_we_custom_image" data-resize-width="undefined" loading="lazy"/>
                  </div>
                  <div class="o_grid_item o_grid_item_image o_snippet_mobile_invisible g-height-4 g-col-lg-8 col-lg-8 d-lg-block d-none o_colored_level" style="z-index: 5; grid-area: 10 / 5 / 14 / 13;">
                    <img src="/web/image/museum.ir_attachment_1583" alt="a black and white photo of a building made of concrete blocks" class="img img-fluid o_we_custom_image" data-resize-width="undefined" loading="lazy"/>
                  </div>
                  <div class="o_grid_item g-col-lg-5 o_colored_level g-height-6 col-lg-5" style="z-index: 1; --grid-item-padding-x: 24px; grid-area: 3 / 8 / 9 / 13;">
                    <h1 class="display-4">
                      <strong>Stories in Space, Time, and Image</strong>
                    </h1>
                    <p class="lead"><br/>Each exhibition is a temporary space of reflection,&amp;nbsp;from long-standing collections to new voices, we invite you to enter, pause, and look again</p>
                    <p>
                      <a class="btn btn-primary" t-att-href="request.env.ref('museum.event_event_4').website_url">Plan your visit</a>
                      <br/>
                    </p>
                  </div>
                </div>
              </div>
            </section>
            <div class="s_hr pt32 pb32 o_colored_level" data-snippet="s_hr" data-name="Separator">
              <hr class="w-100 mx-auto"/>
            </div>
            <section class="s_text_image o_cc o_cc2 o_colored_level pt40 pb40" data-snippet="s_image_text" data-name="Text - Image">
              <div class="container">
                <div class="row align-items-center">
                  <div class="col-lg-6 pt16 pb16 o_colored_level">
                    <img src="/web/image/museum.ir_attachment_1580" alt="gray and blue illustration" class="img img-fluid mx-auto rounded o_we_custom_image" data-resize-width="undefined" loading="lazy"/>
                  </div>
                  <div class="col-lg-5 offset-lg-1 pt16 pb16 o_colored_level">
                    <h1 class="display-3">Melting Silence</h1>
                    <p><em>Melting Silence</em> is a haunting, immersive exhibition by Dutch multimedia artist <strong>Ingrid Baas</strong>, whose work captures the fragile tension between inner stillness and global upheaval. At its core, <em>Melting Silence</em> is an invitation to witness what often goes unheard — the quiet collapse of ecosystems, the slow erosion of memory, and the muted anxiety of a world in flux.</p>
                    <p>Through abstract sculpture, sound installations, and light-responsive media, Baas meditates on the sensory and emotional fallout of the <strong>climate crisis</strong>. The title alludes both to the physical reality of melting glaciers and the psychological stillness that follows collective trauma. Silence becomes both a metaphor for neglect and a canvas for resistance — a space where unspoken grief and subtle transformation coexist.</p>
                    <p>The exhibition is arranged as a gradual descent into softness, with shifting light, ambient tones, and suspended forms encouraging visitors to slow down, observe, and feel. Each piece echoes the urgency of environmental degradation but resists spectacle. Instead, Baas offers <em>silence as a form of protest</em>, a quiet yet powerful reckoning with the Anthropocene.</p>
                  </div>
                </div>
              </div>
            </section>
            <section class="s_text_image o_colored_level o_cc o_cc2 pt32 pb56" data-snippet="s_text_image" data-name="Text - Image">
              <div class="container">
                <div class="row o_grid_mode" data-row-count="11">
                  <div class="o_colored_level o_grid_item g-col-lg-5 g-height-11 col-lg-5 o_grid_item_image" style="z-index: 2; grid-area: 1 / 8 / 12 / 13;">
                    <img src="/web/image/museum.ir_attachment_1585" alt="woman covering her body" class="img img-fluid mx-auto rounded o_we_custom_image" data-mimetype="image/webp" data-original-id="1155" data-original-src="/unsplash/piIgyF0-gcY/artist.jpg?unique=fb21b2fd" data-mimetype-before-conversion="image/jpeg" data-x="-1.5932753899671736e-13" data-y="47.649635036496356" data-width="1568" data-height="1572.4379562043796" data-scale-x="1" data-scale-y="1" data-aspect-ratio="0/0" loading="lazy"/>
                  </div>
                  <div class="o_colored_level o_grid_item g-col-lg-6 g-height-8 col-lg-6" style="z-index: 1; grid-area: 3 / 1 / 11 / 7;">
                    <h2 class="h3-fs">About the artist</h2>
                    <p>
                      <br/>
                    </p>
                    <p><strong>Ingrid Baas</strong> is internationally recognized for her interdisciplinary practice that blends sound art, minimalist sculpture, and sustainable materials. Deeply influenced by northern European landscapes and her early studies in environmental philosophy, Baas creates contemplative environments that draw attention to the unseen — whether emotional, ecological, or societal.</p>
                    <p>Her works have been exhibited in Rotterdam, Oslo, Tokyo, and São Paulo, and she continues to advocate for the integration of environmental ethics into artistic practice.</p>
                    <p>
                      <br/>
                    </p>
                  </div>
                </div>
              </div>
            </section>
            <section class="s_three_columns o_cc pt32 pb32 o_colored_level o_cc1" data-vxml="001" data-vcss="001" data-snippet="s_three_columns" data-name="Columns">
              <div class="container">
                <div class="row d-flex align-items-stretch">
                  <div data-name="Card" class="col-lg-4 pt16 pb16">
                    <div class="s_card o_card_img_top card h-100 o_cc o_cc1 my-0 o_colored_level" data-vxml="001" data-snippet="s_card" data-name="Card">
                      <figure class="o_card_img_wrapper ratio ratio-16x9 mb-0">
                        <img src="/web/image/museum.ir_attachment_1586" alt="abstract painting" class="o_card_img card-img-top img img-fluid o_we_custom_image" data-resize-width="undefined" loading="lazy"/>
                      </figure>
                      <div class="card-body">
                        <h5 class="card-title">
        Silent Waves&amp;nbsp;<br/></h5>
                        <p class="card-text">
        A room-sized kinetic sculpture made from translucent bioplastics and motion-sensitive sound, reflecting the steady collapse of Arctic ice.&amp;nbsp;<br/></p>
                      </div>
                    </div>
                  </div>
                  <div data-name="Card" class="col-lg-4 pt16 pb16">
                    <div class="s_card o_card_img_top card h-100 o_cc o_cc1 my-0 o_colored_level" data-vxml="001" data-snippet="s_card" data-name="Card">
                      <figure class="o_card_img_wrapper ratio ratio-16x9 mb-0">
                        <img src="/web/image/museum.ir_attachment_1587" alt="teal and grey textile" class="o_card_img card-img-top img img-fluid o_we_custom_image" data-resize-width="undefined" loading="lazy"/>
                      </figure>
                      <div class="card-body">
                        <h5 class="card-title">
        Echoes in Grey&amp;nbsp;<br/></h5>
                        <p/>
                        <p>Charcoal on recycled textile with embedded audio of melting ice and wind patterns from Greenland, rendered into slow, rhythmic pulses.</p>
                      </div>
                    </div>
                  </div>
                  <div data-name="Card" class="col-lg-4 pt16 pb16">
                    <div class="s_card card h-100 o_cc o_cc1 my-0 o_colored_level o_card_img_top" data-vxml="001" data-snippet="s_card" data-name="Card">
                      <figure class="o_card_img_wrapper ratio mb-0 ratio-16x9">
                        <img src="/web/image/museum.ir_attachment_1588" alt="aerial photography of brown and gray sand" class="o_card_img img img-fluid o_we_custom_image card-img-top" data-resize-width="undefined" loading="lazy"/>
                      </figure>
                      <div class="card-body">
                        <h5 class="card-title">&amp;nbsp;Frozen Breath </h5>
                        <p class="card-text">
        A suspended glass and resin piece shaped like exhaled air in cold temperatures; delicate and almost invisible, it addresses the fragility of human and planetary breath.&amp;nbsp;<br/></p>
                      </div>
                    </div>
                  </div>
                </div>
              </div>
            </section>
            <div class="s_hr pt32 pb32 o_colored_level" data-snippet="s_hr" data-name="Separator">
              <hr class="w-100 mx-auto"/>
            </div>
            <section class="s_text_image o_cc o_cc2 o_colored_level pt40 pb32" data-snippet="s_image_text" data-name="Text - Image">
              <div class="container">
                <div class="row align-items-center">
                  <div class="col-lg-6 pt16 pb16 o_colored_level">
                    <img src="/web/image/museum.ir_attachment_1581" alt="person foot under painting" class="img img-fluid mx-auto rounded o_we_custom_image" data-resize-width="undefined" loading="lazy"/>
                  </div>
                  <div class="pt16 pb16 o_colored_level col-lg-6">
                    <h1 class="display-3">Voices Across Borders</h1>
                    <p>
                      <strong>Art confronting migration, identity, and displacement</strong>
                    </p>
                    <p><em>Voices Across Borders</em> is not a celebration. It’s an encounter — with stories often left unheard, with systems that draw lines between lives, and with the artists who refuse to look away.</p>
                    <p>This annual event brings together our partners, visitors, and community for a night of critical dialogue through art. It’s a space to question, to listen, and to reflect on the realities of forced movement, cultural erasure, and the search for home.</p>
                    <p>What to expect:</p>
                    <ul>
                      <li>
New installations and works that center lived experience
</li>
                      <li>
A direct conversation with the featured artist
</li>
                      <li>
A look at upcoming exhibitions tied to migration and power structures
</li>
                      <li>
Public readings, workshops, and open dialogue
</li>
                    </ul>
                    <p>This event also offers a moment of transparency: what the museum is working on, how we collaborate, and where we’re accountable.</p>
                  </div>
                </div>
              </div>
            </section>
            <section class="s_text_image o_colored_level o_cc o_cc2 pb56 pt56" data-snippet="s_text_image" data-name="Text - Image">
              <div class="container">
                <div class="row o_grid_mode" data-row-count="11">
                  <div class="o_colored_level o_grid_item g-col-lg-5 g-height-11 col-lg-5 o_grid_item_image" style="z-index: 2; grid-area: 1 / 8 / 12 / 13;">
                    <img src="/web/image/museum.ir_attachment_1589" alt="man in black t-shirt smoking cigarette" class="img img-fluid mx-auto rounded o_we_custom_image" data-mimetype="image/webp" data-original-id="1157" data-original-src="/unsplash/DvaOIjkrQTI/artist.jpg?unique=cbf69caa" data-mimetype-before-conversion="image/jpeg" data-resize-width="NaN" loading="lazy"/>
                  </div>
                  <div class="o_colored_level o_grid_item g-col-lg-6 g-height-8 col-lg-6" style="z-index: 1; grid-area: 3 / 1 / 11 / 7;">
                    <h2 class="h3-fs">About the artist</h2>
                    <p>
                      <br/>
                    </p>
                    <p>Tomás Rivera is a multidisciplinary artist based in Mexico City. His work addresses state violence, migration policy, and the fragility of identity in transit. Through invisible ink, fragmented documents, and found materials, Rivera reconstructs the silence left by displacement.</p>
                    <p>His installation <em>Shadow Passport</em> uses UV-reactive media to expose what official records conceal: fear, loss, and resistance. Rivera doesn’t illustrate migration — he materializes its bureaucracy, its weight, and its aftermath.</p>
                    <p>
</p>
                    <p>This work doesn’t offer closure — it demands witness.</p>
                    <p>
                      <br/>
                    </p>
                  </div>
                </div>
              </div>
            </section>
            <section class="s_three_columns o_cc pt32 pb32 o_colored_level o_cc1" data-vxml="001" data-vcss="001" data-snippet="s_three_columns" data-name="Columns">
              <div class="container">
                <div class="row d-flex align-items-stretch">
                  <div data-name="Card" class="col-lg-4 pt16 pb16">
                    <div class="s_card o_card_img_top card h-100 o_cc o_cc1 my-0 o_colored_level" data-vxml="001" data-snippet="s_card" data-name="Card">
                      <figure class="o_card_img_wrapper ratio ratio-16x9 mb-0">
                        <img src="/web/image/museum.ir_attachment_1590" alt="woman illustration painting" class="o_card_img card-img-top img img-fluid o_we_custom_image" data-mimetype="image/webp" data-original-id="1158" data-original-src="/unsplash/Wa9ilX9XYOI/art.jpg?unique=f79cf5e0" data-mimetype-before-conversion="image/jpeg" data-resize-width="NaN" loading="lazy"/>
                      </figure>
                      <div class="card-body">
                        <h5 class="card-title">
        Shadow Passport&amp;nbsp;<br/></h5>
                        <p class="card-text">
        Invisible borders, hidden identities. Documents that surface only when seen with care.&amp;nbsp;<br/></p>
                      </div>
                    </div>
                  </div>
                  <div data-name="Card" class="col-lg-4 pt16 pb16">
                    <div class="s_card o_card_img_top card h-100 o_cc o_cc1 my-0 o_colored_level" data-vxml="001" data-snippet="s_card" data-name="Card">
                      <figure class="o_card_img_wrapper ratio ratio-16x9 mb-0">
                        <img src="/web/image/museum.ir_attachment_1591" alt="woman with hands tied" class="o_card_img card-img-top img img-fluid o_we_custom_image" data-resize-width="undefined" loading="lazy"/>
                      </figure>
                      <div class="card-body">
                        <h5 class="card-title">
        Holding Distance&amp;nbsp;<br/></h5>
                        <p class="card-text">
        A metaphor for distance and desire. Hands gripping the unseen weight of ambition and exile.&amp;nbsp;<br/></p>
                      </div>
                    </div>
                  </div>
                  <div data-name="Card" class="col-lg-4 pt16 pb16">
                    <div class="s_card o_card_img_top card h-100 o_cc o_cc1 my-0 o_colored_level" data-vxml="001" data-snippet="s_card" data-name="Card">
                      <figure class="o_card_img_wrapper ratio ratio-16x9 mb-0">
                        <img src="/web/image/museum.ir_attachment_1592" alt="grayscale photo of man in black jacket holding black smartphone" class="o_card_img card-img-top img img-fluid o_we_custom_image" data-resize-width="undefined" loading="lazy"/>
                      </figure>
                      <div class="card-body">
                        <h5 class="card-title">
        The Right to Repeat&amp;nbsp;<br/></h5>
                        <p class="card-text">
        Words passed through power. A forgotten text, reprinted — still asking who gets to speak.</p>
                      </div>
                    </div>
                  </div>
                </div>
              </div>
            </section>
            <div class="s_hr pt32 pb32 o_colored_level" data-snippet="s_hr" data-name="Separator">
              <hr class="w-100 mx-auto"/>
            </div>
            <section class="s_text_image o_cc o_cc2 o_colored_level pt48 pb48" data-snippet="s_image_text" data-name="Text - Image">
              <div class="container">
                <div class="row align-items-center">
                  <div class="pt16 pb16 o_colored_level col-lg-5">
                    <img src="/web/image/museum.ir_attachment_1582" alt="a painting of two women in bed looking out a window" class="img img-fluid mx-auto rounded o_we_custom_image" data-resize-width="undefined" loading="lazy"/>
                  </div>
                  <div class="pt16 pb16 o_colored_level col-lg-7">
                    <h1 class="display-2">
                      <span class="display-4-fs">101 Masterpieces that will change the way you see art</span>
                    </h1>
                    <p>
                      <br/>
                    </p>
                    <p>This exhibition brings together 101 transformative works that changed the course of art history. From iconic paintings to daring contemporary interventions, these pieces challenge, provoke, and redefine what art can be. A celebration of bold vision and enduring influence.</p>
                  </div>
                </div>
              </div>
            </section>
            <div class="s_hr pt32 pb32 o_colored_level" data-snippet="s_hr" data-name="Separator">
              <hr class="w-100 mx-auto"/>
            </div>
            <section class="s_text_image o_cc o_cc2 pb112 o_colored_level pt48" data-snippet="s_image_text" data-name="Text - Image">
              <div class="container">
                <div class="row o_grid_mode" data-row-count="9">
                  <div class="o_colored_level o_grid_item g-col-lg-7 g-height-7 col-lg-7" style="z-index: 0; grid-area: 2 / 1 / 9 / 8;">
                    <h1 class="display-2">
                      <span class="display-2-fs">Fragments of a Forgotten City</span>
                      <br/>
                    </h1>
                    <p>
                      <br/>
                    </p>
                    <p>A multi-artist exhibition exploring the traces of cities altered by time, conflict, and migration. Through photography, video, and installation, it reflects on what remains — and what is rebuilt — when a place begins to disappear.</p>
                  </div>
                  <div class="o_colored_level o_grid_item g-col-lg-5 g-height-9 col-lg-5 o_grid_item_image" style="z-index: 1; grid-area: 1 / 8 / 10 / 13;">
                    <img src="/web/image/museum.ir_attachment_1583" alt="a black and white photo of a building made of concrete blocks" class="img img-fluid mx-auto rounded o_we_custom_image" data-resize-width="undefined" loading="lazy"/>
                  </div>
                </div>
              </div>
            </section>
          </div>
        </t>
      </t>
    </field>
